        <h2 id="commitment">Our Commitment to Accessibility</h2>
        <p>Hudson Valley Ticks is committed to ensuring digital accessibility for all visitors. We believe that everyone deserves equal access to health and safety information, regardless of ability or disability.</p>
        
        <p>We actively work to maintain and improve the accessibility of our website in accordance with internationally recognized standards.</p>

        <h2 id="compliance">WCAG 2.1 Level AA Compliance</h2>
        <p>We aim to meet the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1 Level AA standard, which is the most widely recommended level of digital accessibility. This means our website:</p>
        
        <ul>
            <li>Is navigable using keyboard alone (no mouse required)</li>
            <li>Works with screen readers (NVDA, JAWS, VoiceOver)</li>
            <li>Has sufficient color contrast for readability</li>
            <li>Uses clear, descriptive headings and links</li>
            <li>Includes alt text for all images</li>
            <li>Is fully responsive on mobile devices</li>
            <li>Has readable fonts and adjustable text sizing</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="features">Accessibility Features</h2>

        <h3>Keyboard Navigation</h3>
        <p>All interactive elements (links, buttons, forms) are accessible using keyboard navigation:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Tab:</strong> Move forward through interactive elements</li>
            <li><strong>Shift + Tab:</strong> Move backward through interactive elements</li>
            <li><strong>Enter:</strong> Activate links and buttons</li>
            <li><strong>Escape:</strong> Close menus and modals</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Screen Reader Support</h3>
        <p>Our website is tested with popular screen readers including:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>NVDA (Windows, free)</li>
            <li>JAWS (Windows, commercial)</li>
            <li>VoiceOver (macOS, iOS, built-in)</li>
            <li>TalkBack (Android, built-in)</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Color Contrast</h3>
        <p>All text meets or exceeds WCAG AA standards for color contrast, ensuring readability for users with low vision or color blindness.</p>

        <h3>Text Sizing</h3>
        <p>You can adjust text size in your browser:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Windows:</strong> Ctrl + Plus to enlarge, Ctrl + Minus to reduce</li>
            <li><strong>macOS:</strong> Cmd + Plus to enlarge, Cmd + Minus to reduce</li>
            <li><strong>Mobile:</strong> Pinch to zoom in/out</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Responsive Design</h3>
        <p>Our website is fully responsive and works on devices of all sizes, from mobile phones to large desktop monitors.</p>

        <h3>Plain Language</h3>
        <p>We use clear, simple language and avoid jargon where possible to make health information accessible to everyone.</p>

        <h2 id="limitations">Known Limitations</h2>
        
        <div class="info-box">
            <strong>Amazon Affiliate Links:</strong> Links to Amazon may have some accessibility limitations as they are hosted on third-party servers. We recommend using Amazon's accessibility features if you have questions about specific products.
        </div>

        <p>We are continuously working to identify and fix any accessibility issues. If you encounter any barriers, please report them using the contact information below.</p>

        <h2 id="contact">Report Accessibility Issues</h2>
        
        <p>If you experience difficulty accessing any part of Hudson Valley Ticks, please contact us:</p>
        
        <div class="info-box">
            <strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:accessibility@hudsonvalleyticks.com">accessibility@hudsonvalleyticks.com</a><br>
            <strong>Subject:</strong> "Accessibility Issue"<br>
            <strong>Include:</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>Which page or feature you were trying to access</li>
                <li>What assistive technology you were using (screen reader, keyboard, etc.)</li>
                <li>What the problem was</li>
                <li>Your browser and operating system</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <p>We will respond to accessibility issues within 5 business days and work to resolve them as quickly as possible.</p>

